attributes.PROJECT_FULL_TITLE: GT CCS Croatia – construction of pipeline transport infrastructure in Croatia and Hungary, with underground storage in HR
attributes.TECHNICAL_DESCR:
Geothermal CCS Croatia concerns the transport and permanent storage of CO2 from emitters in Croatia and Hungary, located along the HR-HU border.

The project is designed in such a way that the operator of the transport system will take over the captured CO2 from emitters, mainly cement plants in Hungary and Croatia, and transport it via pipelines to the site of the injection plant in Bockovac, Osječko-baranjska County, Republic of Croatia.

The infrastructure elements comprising this PCI are:

- Dedicated pipelines collecting CO2 from emitters in Croatia and Hungary, excluding upstream.

- Fixed facilities for liquefaction, buffer storage and CO2 converters in the CO2 storage area per below.

- Surface and injection facilities associated to the onshore CO2 storage field in in Bockovac, Croatia.

- Any equipment or installation for the operation of the project, including protection, control and monitoring systems.

At this stage, the estimated capacity of permanent store is 15.77 Mt of CO2 at this site over a period of 25 years.
attributes.IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS_DESCR: Planned but not yet in permitting
